Client persistence (Zustand)

No raw localStorage / sessionStorage in UI

Do not read or write window.localStorage or window.sessionStorage directly in components, hooks (except store internals), or scattered lib helpers for product state.
Use Zustand for client-only state that must persist or be shared across the tree. For persistence, use the persist middleware (or an equivalent documented pattern) so reads/writes stay typed, testable, and centralized.

Feature store/ layout

Per feature, put stores and store-specific helpers under src/features/<feature>/store/ (e.g. chat-persistence.store.ts, chat-persistence.storage.ts).
One store module per file when practical; colocate custom persist storage adapters next to that store — not in components. Add migrations only when you intentionally need to evolve persisted shape (avoid unless required).

Types and validation

Persisted JSON from the browser must be validated with Zod before use (see zod-validation). Colocate *.schema.ts under feature schemas/ next to the store when it describes persisted state.
Public store types live in feature types/ (e.g. chat-persistence.types.ts), often re-exporting z.infer from the schema for a single source of truth.

Hydration (Next.js)

After persist, wait for persist.hasHydrated() / onFinishHydration before trusting rehydrated values for routing or bootstrap (see use-chat-persistence-hydrated). Avoid flashing wrong UI from default state before storage has replayed.
